article.headline: Lady Techsters double up on hapless UTEP
article.linkText: Louisiana Tech doubles up UTEP, sends a message
article.story:
RUSTON, La. (AP) -- Louisiana Tech head coach Kurt Budke wanted his team to make a statement, and they did.

Trina Frierson scored 20 points to lead five players in double figures, as No. 6 Louisiana Tech cruised in a 108-54 rout of Texas-El Paso on Thursday night.

"We talked about coming out and protecting our lead, playing
strong, and showing the nation we belonged,'' Budke said.

Cheryl Ford added 17 points and pulled down eight rebounds for
the Lady Techsters (24-2, 16-0 Western Athletic Conference). Erica
Smith had 13 points and Amber Obaze and Toya George each scored 12.

   Tech jumped out to a 12-0 lead in the first three minutes thanks
to a pair of three-pointers by Smith, and increased it to 24-4 at
the 13:46 mark of the first half. The Lady Techsters made 54
percent (21-of-39) of their field goals in the opening half to grab
a commanding 55-22 halftime lead.

"Everyone knows we have struggled at home this year,'' said
Frierson, who recorded her third 20-plus point outing in her last
four games despite playing only 21 minutes. "We wanted to come out
from the beginning and follow the game plan and make sure we
defended UTEP. We knew they could score. Things just worked out to
our advantage.''

Ingrid Goslin was the only player to score in double figures for
UTEP (10-15, 5-10). She finished with 10 points.

Louisiana Tech made nearly twice as many shots from the field as
the Miners, hitting 43-of-73 (60 percent) while UTEP finished
22-of-58 (38 percent).

Frierson, who is averaging 23.3 points over the last four contests, said she has played with more confidence recently.

"I'm just looking at things differently,'' Frierson said. "Instead of worrying about every little thing, I get the ball and think I can't be denied. I'm going to do whatever it takes to make this team better.''
